President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of New York due to a severe winter storm that occurred from December 11-31, 2008. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Marianne C. Jackson has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the state and based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-4600.